2.00	Citizen_soldiers	Citizen Soldiers	Citizen Soldiers: The US Army from the Normandy Beaches to the Bulge to the Surrender of Germany is a non-fiction book about World War II written by Stephen E. Ambrose and published in 1997. It deals with Allied soldiers moving in from the Normandy beaches, and through Europe (between June 7, 1944 and May 7, 1945). In addition to telling short stories of countless soldiers experiencing the war, the author also explains the events before telling the stories. He interviewed dozens of soldiers in the making of the book.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/81/Citizen_Soldiers.jpg/200px-Citizen_Soldiers.jpg
